In a speech delivered at Yokota Air Base in Japan, Vice President Mike Pence expressed gratitude to the American and Japanese military personnel stationed there. He praised their courage and selflessness, and emphasized the importance of the US-Japan alliance in maintaining peace, prosperity, and freedom in the Indo-Pacific region. Pence also addressed the threat posed by North Korea, criticizing its regime for subjugating its own people and engaging in nuclear and ballistic missile development. He reaffirmed the US commitment to intensify economic and diplomatic pressure on North Korea until it abandons its weapons programs. Pence emphasized that the US is ready to defend its homeland and allies, and highlighted the strength and capabilities of the US military. He concluded by expressing confidence in the future security, prosperity, and peace of both the US and Japan.